      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WARILLA GORILLA (2) was an impressive winner last time over 1200m at Toowoomba, stalking the pace before lengthening nicely to score by 5.5 lengths as favourite. Will go forward again and draws better. Keeps Butler and can go on with the job. POWERFUL EAGLE (1) ran a much better race beaten 3.5 lengths over 1350m at Warwick. Led them up and keeps the handy 3kg claim. Peaks and will give a big sight using the inside barrier. SON OF BEEBEE (4) won a 60 at Gatton this trip and then was slow away and didn't finish it off over a mile at Toowoomba. Has a 3kg claim and has been kept up to the mark with a Gatton trial placing. Worth another chance back 200m. BEST COFFEE (5) resumed a comfortable 55 win over 1200m at Kilcoy. Proven second-up and with the weight relief has to be considered.",
